The paper focuses on deep reinforcement learning for training robots to perform complex tasks in the real world, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of domain randomisation for training agents in simulation is a popular method in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the trained agents' generalisation abilities involves visuomotor control tasks, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the examination of the agents' weights and activations is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
